{"TopicId":128277,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Make lower layers of Jool\u0026#039;s atmosphere deadly hot","CreatedByName":"Wjolcz","CreatedById":39636,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-20T19:01:38Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Wjolcz","CreatedById":39636,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-20T19:01:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe lowest parts of the atmosphere shouldn\u0027t be accessible. Everything that gets there should explode from the heat. Just so it\u0027s not that easy to reach the \u0022surface\u0022 and summon the kraken.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"wizzlebippi","CreatedById":85324,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-20T23:13:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI had never thought of trying to send a probe into Jool until I read this.\u00A0 Now that I have, I agree.\u00A0 It either needs to crush or melt the ship going for the middle of Jool.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NathanKell","CreatedById":75006,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-20T23:14:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust not that hot.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPressure, now...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wjolcz","CreatedById":39636,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-20T23:21:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222330595\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022128277\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221450653293\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002275006\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022NathanKell\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, NathanKell said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust not that hot.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPressure, now...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, I know the temperatures there wouldn\u0027t be realistic, but since there are no pressure effects in the game it would be nice to have some other force of destruction that would prevent the vessels from landing there. At least for now. Pwetty pwease? :3\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222015-12-20T23:23:34Z\u0022 title=\u002212/20/2015 11:23  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 20, 2015\u003C/time\u003E by Veeltch\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KerbonautInTraining","CreatedById":145373,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-20T23:28:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt would be kind of like trying to crash a probe into the Sun, I\u0027d imagine.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nikokespprfan","CreatedById":136115,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-21T16:47:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222330602\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022128277\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221450653668\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002239636\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Veeltch\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 hours ago, Veeltch said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, I know the temperatures there wouldn\u0027t be realistic, but since there are no pressure effects in the game it would be nice to have some other force of destruction that would prevent the vessels from landing there. At least for now. Pwetty pwease? :3\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr you just leet it explode, just like it does when it comes too close to \u003Cs\u003Ethe sun\u003C/s\u003E kerbol, but instead of the yellow message mentioning heat, it mentions pressure.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"swjr-swis","CreatedById":152460,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-21T18:42:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222330595\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022128277\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221450653293\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002275006\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022NathanKell\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n19 hours ago, NathanKell said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust not that hot.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLiquid metallic hydrogen can get pretty hot...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}